[4] Bolivia
Date: Thu 22 Oct 2009
Source: Prensa Latina [in Portuguese, trans & summ. Mod.TY, edited]
<http://www.prensa-latina.cu/index.php?option=com_content&task=view&id=130831&Itemid=75>


The Bolivian President, Evo Morales, today [22 Oct 2009] urged that
citizens and regional authorities adopt measures to avoid a new
dengue epidemic in the country. "The best approach to human health
care is prevention," said the head of state in a public event in
Santa Cruz department [state or province equivalent], where he
delivered ambulances, medicines, and fumigation equipment as part of
a national campaign against this disease.

Up to now, 4 confirmed cases of classical dengue have been confirmed
in Santa Cruz and Beni departments. The arrival of the rainy season
in Bolivia is worrying health officials facing the risk of
reappearance of this disease, including its more lethal form, DHF.

Among the preventive measures adopted, underlining its importance, is
eradication of conditions for reproduction of the vector, the
mosquito _Aedes aegypti_, and fumigation, tasks provided with the
help of the armed forces.

Last year [2008], Bolivia suffered the worst dengue epidemic in the
past 20 years in the country, which caused the deaths of 22 people.

