[6] Brazil (Mato Grosso)
Date: Thu 22 Oct 2009
Source: So Noticias, A Gazeta report [in Portuguese, trans. Mod.TY, edited]
<http://www.sonoticias.com.br/noticias/11/95206/mato-grosso-registra-69-casos-de-dengue-em-uma-semana>


In 7 days, Mato Grosso had 69 new notifications of dengue, and only 1
[case] of the serious form of the disease. The bulletin released by
the state Secretariat of Health pointed out that now there are 38 726
reported [cases], with 1107 cases of [dengue] with complications.
There were also 38 cases of deaths due to dengue, of which 32 were
confirmed cases and 6 cases are under investigation. The state had an
increase of 265 percent of reported dengue [cases] compared the same
period of 2008.

Given the situation faced by public health of the state in relation
to dengue this year [2009], the government has mobilized to try to
prevent a new outbreak of the disease, which struck mainly the city
of Cuiaba with 11 118 dengue patients, of which 311 were serious
cases. There have been 13 deaths registered (8 confirmed [as dengue]
and 5 under investigation). Other municipalities that have confirmed
deaths due to this disease up to now are Curvelandia (1 [death]),
Diamantino (1), Jaciara (1), Juara (1), Nova Mutum (1), Rondonopolis
(2), Rosario Oeste (2), Sinop (5), Tangara da Serra (2), Tapurah (1),
and Varzea Grande (7).

Next week [week of 26 Oct 2009], the state and the municipalities of
Cuiaba and Varzea Grande will start a campaign for cleanliness in the
backyards of the houses.

--
